                    <h3 class="h3-title">MENTAL HEALTH COUNSELOR</h3>
                    <h2 class="h2-title">IQRA NAZ</h2>
                    <div class="col-md">
                        <p>I am an experienced mental health counselor with extensive training at 
                            various mental health facilities and over 2 years of experience working
                            privately. My area of interests and expertise includes depression, 
                            anxiety, interpersonal conflicts, grief/loss and issues related life 
                            adjustment in various contexts.</p>
                        <p>I believe that counseling/therapy is not limited to an individual 
                            struggling with a serious mental health issue, rather, it is for any 
                            individual who wants to explore his/herself. If one feels the need for 
                            assistance to navigate through difficult emotions and equip themselves 
                            with the tools to live a meaningful life then therapy is the best place 
                            to achieve that. It is learning to exist in a way that allows us to 
                            experience all human emotions in a balanced manner and foster personal growth.</p>
                        <p>While my approach to counseling is primarily Cognitive Behavioral Therapy I
                            do however use other therapuetic approaches as well, depending upon the 
                            difficulties my clients are facing. I adopt a Narrative approach to 
                            understand and explore how we construct our realities and how these 
                            narratives about ourselves and the world around us influences behaviors 
                            and emotions.</p> 
                    </div>
                    <div class="col-md">
                        <img class="profile-img" src="assets/img/Iqra Naz-min.webp">
                        <p>My greatest strength is that I try to deliver the most 
                            ethical care I can to my clients, this includes regular supervision and 
                            staying informed about new developments in the field. The therapeutic 
                            alliance I build with my clients allows them to take ownership of thier 
                            struggles as much as their joy.</p>
                    </div>
